cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is about deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on Atari 2600 games, which are a popular benchmark for testing reinforcement learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper deals with image-based games. The paper also discusses the issue of catastrophic interference, which is a problem in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to improve the performance and data efficiency of deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
